<!-- the abstract for the module. If not provided, the XSL will use the in scope -->
 <abstract>
<li>
		 This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of the information needed to describe a geometric relationship between a geometric model in a two dimensional coordinate
     system and a corresponding model in a three dimensional coordinate system where the relationship is for coordination purposes and not
     for definitional or placement purposes.
</li>
 </abstract>

